  "prompt": "Do I really need to buy tires in pairs?",
  "response": "When it comes to buying tires, it's generally recommended to purchase them in pairs, especially for vehicles with rear-wheel or all-wheel drive. Here are some reasons to consider:\n\n1. **Handling and Stability**: Having tires with similar tread depth and type on each axle helps maintain consistent handling and stability. Uneven tires can lead to unpredictable handling, especially in wet or slippery conditions.\n\n2. **Tread Wear**: If you replace just one tire, the new tire will have deeper tread than the others, which can lead to differences in grip. This is particularly important during cornering or braking.\n\n3. **All-Wheel Drive Vehicles**: For all-wheel-drive vehicles, it\u2019s usually best to have all four tires matched. Mismatched tires can cause issues with the drivetrain and may lead to premature wear or failure.\n\n4. **Cost-effectiveness**: Buying in pairs can often be more economical in the long run, as it allows you to maintain a balanced set of tires that wear at a similar rate.\n\nHowever, if your existing tires are relatively new and in good condition, and the tire you\u2019re replacing is damaged beyond repair, it may be fine to replace only one tire under certain conditions. Always consult your vehicle\u2019s owner manual and consider the type of drive system your vehicle uses before making a decision. If in doubt, consult with a tire professional for personalized advice.",
